03/12/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- An armed man broke into a school in Thessaloniki on Wednesday (December 2nd) and briefly held three hostages before surrendering. 
Police say he told them if he did not receive a huge ransom, he would detonate explosives. 
He eventually agreed to release the hostages and surrendered.
The suspect, identified as Costas Arabatzis, 55, pulled the same stunt at the school three years ago, demanding a 5m-euro ransom. 
In both cases, he was home on leave from prison, where he serving a 19-year sentence for kidnapping. 
(AP, Kathimerini, AFP - 02/12/09)
